:German Canadian]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Canadian English|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|name              = Kitchener\n|settlement_type   = [[List of cities in Ontario|City]] ([[List of municipalities in Ontario#Lower-tier municipalities|lower-tier]])\n|official_name     = City of Kitchener\n|image_skyline     = Arial photo of downtown Kitchener Ontario.JPG\n|image_caption     = View of Downtown Kitchener\n|motto             = ''Ex industria prosperitas'' ({{lang-la|Prosperity through industry}})\n|image_flag        =Flag of Kitchener, Ontario.svg\n|image_blank_emblem= Logo of Kitchener, Ontario.svg\n|blank_emblem_size = 100x90px\n|image_map         = Kitchener, Ontario.png\n|mapsize           = 200px\n|map_caption       = Location of Kitchener in Waterloo Region\n|pushpin_map = Canada Southern Ontario\n|pushpin_map_caption = Location of Kitchener in southern Ontario\n|subdivision_type  = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n|subdivision_type1 = [[Provinces and territories of Canada|Province]]\n|subdivision_name  = [[Canada]]\n|subdivision_name1 = [[Ontario]]\n|subdivision_type2 = [[Census divisions of Ontario|Region]]\n|subdivision_name2 = [[Regional Municipality of Waterloo|Waterloo]]\n|leader_title      = Mayor\n|leader_name = [[Berry Vrbanovic]]\n|leader_title2      = Governing Body\n|leader_name2 = [[Kitchener City Council]]\n|established_title = Founded\n|established_date  = 1833\n|established_title1= Incorporated\n|established_date1 = 1853\n|established_title2= Incorporated\n|established_date2 = 1912 (city)\n|area_footnotes    = <ref name=SC06/><ref name=SC06-ca/><ref>{{cite web |title=Census Profile, 2016 Census |url=https://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2016/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=POPC&Code1=0419&Geo2=PR&Code2=35&SearchText=Kitchener&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&B1=All&GeoLevel=PR&GeoCode=0419&TABID=1&type=0 |website=Statistics Canada |publisher=Statistics Canada |accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n|area_magnitude    = 1 E8\n|area_total_km2    = 136.89\n|area_land_km2     = 136.89\n|area_water_km2    =\n|area_urban_km2    = 269.23\n|area_metro_km2    = 1,091.16\n|population_as_of  = 2016\n|population_footnotes = <ref name=SC06>{{cite web |url=http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2016/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=CSD&Code1=3530013&Geo2=CD&Code2=3530&Data=Count&SearchText=kitchener&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&B1=All&TABID=1 |title=Kitchener (city) census profile |publisher=[[Statistics Canada]] |work=[[Canada 2016 Census|2016 Census data]] |accessdate=12 February 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170213090426/http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2016/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=CSD&Code1=3530013&Geo2=CD&Code2=3530&Data=Count&SearchText=kitchener&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&B1=All&TABID=1 |archivedate=13 February 2017 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n<ref name=SC06-ca>{{cite web |url=http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2016/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=CMACA&Code1=541&Geo2=PR&Code2=35&Data=Count&SearchText=kitchener&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&B1=All&TABID=1 |title=Kitchener \u2013 Cambridge \u2013 Waterloo (Census metropolitan area) |publisher=Statistics Canada |work=[[Canada 2016 Census|2016 Census data]] |accessdate=12 February 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170213163802/http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2016/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=CMACA&Code1=541&Geo2=PR&Code2=35&Data=Count&SearchText=kitchener&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&B1=All&TABID=1 |archivedate=13 February 2017 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=SC06/><ref name=SC06-ca/><ref>{{cite web |title=Census Profile, 2016 Census |url=https://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2016/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=POPC&Code1=0419&Geo2=PR&Code2=35&SearchText=Kitchener&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&B1=All&GeoLevel=PR&GeoCode=0419&TABID=1&type=0 |website=Statistics Canada |publisher=Statistics Canada |accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n|population_urban  = 470015 ([[List of the 100 largest municipalities in Canada by population|10th]])\n|population_metro  = 523,894 ([[List of the 100 largest metropolitan areas in Canada|10th]])\n|population_density_urban_km2 = 1745.8\n|population_density_metro_km2 = 480.1\n|postal_code_type       = [[Canadian postal code#Forward sortation areas|Forward sortation area]]\n|postal_code            = [[List of N postal codes of Canada|N2A to N2H, N2M to N2R]]\n|area_codes         = [[Area codes 519, 226 and 548|519, 226 and 548]]\n|timezone          = [[North American Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n|utc_offset        = \u22125\n|coordinates       = {{coord|43|25|07|N|80|28|22|W|region:CA-ON|display=inline,title}}\n|timezone_DST      = [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]]\n|utc_offset_DST    = \u22124\n|blank1_name = [[Geographical Names Board of Canada|GNBC]] Code\n|blank1_info = FEBWC<ref name=\"GNBC\">{{cite web | title = Kitchener | publisher = Natural Resources Canada | date = October 6, 2016 | url = http://www4.rncan.gc.ca/search-place-names/unique/FEBWC}}</ref>\n|website           = [http://www.kitchener.ca/ www.kitchener.ca]\n|footnotes         =\t\n|population_demonym= Kitchenerite\n\n}}\n\n'''Kitchener''' is a city in the [[Regional Municipality of Waterloo]], [[Ontario]]. Located approximately {{convert|100|km|mi|abbr=on}} west of [[Toronto]], Kitchener is the regional seat. Kitchener was called '''[[Berlin to Kitchener name change|Berlin]]''' until 1916; it was designated the Town of Berlin from 1854 until 1912 and the City of Berlin from 1912 until 1916.\n\nThe City of Kitchener covers an area of 136.86 square kilometres and had a population of 233,222 at the time of the [[Canada 2016 Census|2016 Census]]. The Kitchener [[Tri-Cities (Ontario)|metropolitan area]], which includes the smaller, neighbouring cities of [[Waterloo, Ontario|Waterloo]] to the north and [[Cambridge, Ontario|Cambridge]] to the south, has 523,894 people, making it the tenth largest [[Census Metropolitan Area]] (CMA) in Canada and the fourth largest CMA in Ontario.\n\nKitchener and Waterloo are considered \"twin cities\" which are often referred to jointly as \"Kitchener\u2013Waterloo\" (K\u2013W), although they have separate [[Municipal government in Canada|municipal governments]]. Including Cambridge, the three cities are known as \"[[Tri-Cities (Ontario)|the Tri-Cities]]\". All are part of the Regional Municipality of Waterloo, which was created in 1973, when it replaced Waterloo County, which had been created in 1853.\n\n==Geography and climate==\n\n===Geography===\nKitchener is located in [[Southwestern Ontario]], in the [[Saint Lawrence Lowlands]]. This geological and climatic region has wet-climate soils and deciduous forests. Situated in the Grand River Valley, the area is generally above {{convert|300|m|ft|abbr=on|sigfig=1}} in elevation.\n\nKitchener is the largest city within the [[Grand River (Ontario)|Grand River]] watershed, and the largest city on the Haldimand Tract. Just to the west of the city is [[Baden Hill]], in [[Wilmot, Ontario|Wilmot Township]]. This glacial [[kame]] remnant formation is the highest elevation for many miles. The other dominant glacial feature is the [[Waterloo Moraine]], which snakes its way through the region and holds a significant quantity of [[artesian wells]], from which the city derives most of its drinking water. The settlement's first name, Sandhills, is an accurate description of the higher points of the moraine.\n\n===Climate===\nKitchener has a [[humid continental climate]] of the warm summer subtype (''Dfb'' under the [[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]]); there are large seasonal differences, usually warm and humid summers and cold to occasionally very cold winters. Winter-like conditions generally last from the mid-December until mid-March, while summer temperatures generally occur between mid-May to close to the end of September.\n\nMarch 2012 went down in the history books for Kitchener \u2013 between 16 and 22 March, temperatures ranged from {{convert|21.4|C|F|1}} to {{convert|27.0|C|F|1}}\u20147 record highs in a row. 19 March high of {{convert|24|C|F|1}} is one of the highest winter temperatures ever recorded, while 22 March high of {{convert|27|C|F|1}} is the highest for March in this area.\n\nTemperatures during the year can exceed {{convert|30|C|F|1}} in the summer and drop below {{convert|-20|C|F|1}} in the winter several times a year, but prolonged periods of extreme temperatures are rare.  The frost-free period for Kitchener averages about 147 frost-free days a year,<ref name=climate /> a much lower number than cities on the Great Lakes due its inland location and higher elevation. Snowfall averages {{convert|160|cm|in|0}}  per year; this is high, but not nearly as high as areas more directly affected by [[lake effect snow]].\n\nThe highest temperature ever recorded in Kitchener was {{convert|38.3|C|0}} on August 6 & 7, 1918, and again on July 27, 1941.<ref name=\"August 1918\"/><ref name=\"July 1941\"/> The coldest temperature ever recorded was {{convert|-34.1|C|1}} on February 16, 2015.<ref name=\"February 2015\"/>\n\n{{Weather box\n|location = [[Region of Waterloo International Airport]], 1981\u20132010 normals, extremes 1914\u2013present{{efn|Daily maximum and minimum temperatures and precipitation were recorded at Kitchener from October 1914 to December 1977 and at [[Region of Waterloo International Airport]] from March 1970 to present.<ref name=\"Kitchener\"/><ref name=\"climate\"/>}}\n|metric first = Y\n|single line = Y\n|Jan record high C = 14.2\n|Feb record high C = 16.8\n|Mar record high C = 27.0\n|Apr record high C = 30.0\n|May record high C = 33.3\n|Jun record high C = 36.7\n|Jul record high C = 38.3\n|Aug record high C = 38.3\n|Sep record high C = 36.7\n|Oct record high C = 31.1\n|Nov record high C = 25.0\n|Dec record high C = 18.7\n|year record high C = 3